description: {"blocks":[{"key":"3ilca","text":"Nontuberculous mycobacterial (NTM) were identified using matrix-assisted laser desorption-ionization time of flight mass spectrometry (MALDI-TOF MS), and tests were performed to determine antibiotic susceptibility, the ability to form biofilms, sliding motility characteristics, and the ability to adhere to and invade pneumocyte cells. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
keywords: NTM,Antibiotics Susceptibility Testing,biofilm, sliding motility,Nontuberculous mycobacterial

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1kse1","text":"NTM species identification","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"elkh0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eqjle","text":"NTM colonies were taken from LJ media using a 1 mL loop and put into a 1.5 mL microtube containing 0.5 mm of glass beads and 500 mL of 70% ethanol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b88dh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"20itc","text":"The vortex was carried out for 15 minutes and then incubated vertically at room temperature for 10 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dvvim","text":"Vortex was carried out again, transferred into 2 ml of round-bottomed microtube, and then centrifuged at a speed of 10.000-14.000 g for 2 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4keg5","text":"The supernatant was removed, 10 mL of 70% formic acid was added to the pellet, and then the vortex was carried out until homogeneous.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cv4ig","text":"10 mL of acetonitrile was added, and then vortex was carried out until homogeneous.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9htba","text":"Centrifugation was carried out at a speed of 10.000-14.000 g for 2 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6f25f","text":"NTM sensitivity test to various antibiotics.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"i61a","text":"1 μL of supernatant was taken, placed on the target spot on the slide, and allowed to dry completely.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a7pj7","text":"1 μL of matrix VITEK® MS-CHCA (bioMerieux, USA) was added and allowed to dry until the matrix and isolate crystallized.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dj2q0","text":"The slide was loaded into the VITEK® MS MALDI TOF machine (bioMerieux, USA), and the sample number was added.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4aefa","text":"The results were read using a computer connected to MALDI TOF VITEK® MS (bioMerieux, USA). The identification test results will appear on the monitor in the form of the NTM species name.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"blt9u","text":"Determination of the concentration of the stock of antibiotics was conducted through the dilution process. The dilution was carried out based on the content of each antibiotic used to obtain a final concentration of 1000 mg/mL. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fmjpc","text":"0.1 mL of Middlebrook 7H9 broth was added to each well microdilution plate using a pipette, and one column was left for negative control with a volume of 0.2 mL.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"df8pi","text":"0.1 mL of antibiotic was added to each column, and serial dilution was carried out in each subsequent column, leaving 1 column for positive control.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f2ap5","text":"Bacterial colonies were taken from 3-5 colonies of LJ medium and transferred to the saline solution using a tube until it reached turbidity of 0.5 McFarland (1-2 × 108 CFU/mL).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":166,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"28tda","text":"Diluted suspension of 0.5 McFarland (1-2 × 108 CFU/mL) was carried out using the saline solution in a ratio of 1:20 so that the concentration became 5-10 x 106 CFU/mL, then 0.1 mL was added to each appropriate column, except for the sterile control column.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":45,"length":1},{"style":"sup","offset":158,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ahqff","text":"In each well, around the Microdilution plate, saline was added to keep the atmosphere moist. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a3qrr","text":"The Microdilution plate was wrapped with plastic or plastic tape to prevent dryness.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fda8","text":"Incubation was done at a temperature of 35±2°C for 7 days.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"150i6","text":"Observation of growth was conducted through the growth of bacteria in wells containing antibiotics compared to growth controls.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"40oh2","text":"The test was repeated 3 times, and the MIC value was determined for each test. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"d0un1","text":"Biofilm formation","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6tsg9","text":"Determination was carried out into sensitive (S), intermediate (I), or resistant (R) groups based on the MIC criteria according to Table 1 (see attachment). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"pmns","text":"NTM isolates were grown in Middlebrook 7H9 medium for 24 hours at 370C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":68,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a96qg","text":"Each well of a 96-well microtiter polystyrene plate was filled with 198 mL of Middlebrook 7H9 medium (except the wells in columns 1 and 12, rows A and H) ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7gqee","text":"2 mL of NTM isolate suspension was added into each column filled with media and left 1 column for negative control. In the negative control column, isolate S. epidermidis ATCC 12228 was added.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":156,"length":15}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cqmrm","text":"The wells in columns 1 and 12, rows A and H, were filled with saline to keep the atmosphere moist. The biofilm formation test using a 96-well microtiter polystyrene plate is shown in figure 1 (see attachment)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ev3a7","text":"Incubation was completed at 37°C for 7 days.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"84m5b","text":"The wells were washed three times with 200 mL PBS.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6324p","text":"Adherent cells were stained with 0.1% crystal violet (50 mL), and then washed with distilled water 3 times (using a pipette).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9hruk","text":"The paint was resuspended with 200 mL of 5% isopropanol acid, and then the absorbance was observed at l 595 nm. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"62t69","text":"The bacterial OD value was calculated based on the absorbance value for 6 repetitions carried out in the B-G well. The OD value of bacteria was obtained by calculating the average absorbance value of at least 3 almost the same.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e1h7j","text":"ODc value was calculated, where ODc = Average OD of the negative control + 3x SD of negative control.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"44n2o","text":"The results were interpreted into categories of strong, medium, weak, and unable to form biofilms (negative), as shown in Table 2 (see attachment).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"122de","text":"Ability to perform sliding motility","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2eev8","text":"Sliding motility media was prepared, namely Middlebrook 7H9 (without OADC) and 0.3% agar.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6kd2f","text":"Inoculation of NTM culture was carried out as much as 3 μL at optical density (OD) 600.6 (2.7 × 105 CFU) in the middle of the sliding motility media, and the plate was covered with parafilm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"coghg","text":"Incubation was carried out at 37°C in a 5% CO2 atmosphere for up to 16 days in a humid atmosphere.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":45,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ekh5n","text":"Measurement of the length of the NTM growth area was carried out on days 4, 8, 12, and 16 using digital calipers in mm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4qkhj","text":"The sliding motility test was carried out 3 times.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"39pdc","text":"The average length of growth was calculated from 3 test repetitions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2slss","text":"Ability to perform adhesion and invasion","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"cd8fm","text":"A549 cell line (human type II pneumocyte) culture was carried out.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8gsej","text":"Supplement at DMEM (Invitrogen, Australia) was added with 10% FBS (Bovogen, Australia), 100 mg/mL of streptomycin, and 2 mM of L-glutamine.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ftqbq","text":"Observation of monolayer cell growth was carried out until it reached \u003e95% growth.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1h33e","text":"The monolayer cells were washed with PBS, and about 1x107 CFU of NTM bacteria were added to each well. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":56,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"as3d5","text":"Incubation of A549 cell line (human type II pneumocyte), which had been infected at 37oC for 4 hours, was carried out.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":86,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"an4rk","text":"The culture medium was removed, and 0.25% trypsin was added to the PBS to remove the A549 cell line (human type II pneumocyte) from the well surface.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1j75s","text":"The A549 cell line (human type II pneumocyte), which had been washed using 200 mL of 0.025% sterile Triton X-100, was lysed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bchbe","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1uvo1","text":"20 mL suspension was put into Middlebrook 7H9 medium to determine the amount of bacterial CFU attached to each well. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4jidm","text":"Dilution was carried out for 1000x","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dgj90","text":"Incubation was carried out for 10 days.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fke4v","text":"Bacterial colonies were counted.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1mv5g","text":"Tests were repeated on each species three times at different times. Each time the test was repeated twice.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"dj9e","text":"Observation of NTM biofilm cell structure using SEM","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1s1lb","text":"Bacterial suspension was prepared equivalent to 1 Mc Farland.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6dvc","text":"20 mL of bacterial suspension was put into a 12-well microplate filled with a round cover glass and 1980 l of Middlebrook 7H9 media. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e3e9u","text":"Incubation was carried out at 35-370C for 7 days.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":35,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bjnc8","text":"Wells overgrown with biofilm were washed with PBS 2 times.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"89ueq","text":"The cover glass was taken and rehydrated using ethanol serially (70% for 10 minutes and then 96% for 10 minutes).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cf883","text":"Ethanol was discarded, allowed to dry overnight at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c20jp","text":"The cover glass was taken and coated twice with platinum vanadium using an ion sputter (Bal-Tec SCD 005) for 11 seconds, after which the cover glass was glued to double-side carbon tape to be observed using SEM (JEOL JED-2300, Japan).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
